    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the pan to a medium heat with a small drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and once hot, add the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>onion </strong>with a pinch of<strong> salt </strong>and cook for 5-6 min or until softened</p><p>Meanwhile, dissolve <strong>half </strong>the <strong>chicken</strong> <strong>stock</strong> <strong>mix</strong> (you'll use the rest later!) with the <strong>tomato paste </strong>in 100ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[200ml]</span> <strong>boiled</strong> <strong>water </strong>– this is your <strong>tomato stock</strong></p><p>Once the onion has softened, add the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>grated</strong> <strong>garlic</strong> to the pan and cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p>",
