      "instruction": "<p>Heat a small dry pan over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>flaked</strong> <strong>almonds</strong> and cook for 2-3 min or until toasted and lightly golden</p><p>Tip: Watch them like a hawk to make sure they don’t burn!</p><p>Once toasted, add the <strong>remaining ras el hanout </strong>with a pinch of<strong> salt</strong>, then transfer to a small bowl with the <strong>remaining chopped mint</strong> – these are your <strong>spiced</strong> <strong>mint</strong> <strong>almonds</strong></p>",
